  "stem": "<p class=\"para_center\"><span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"D equals, T minus, the fraction 9 over 25, end fraction, times open parenthesis, 100 minus H, close parenthesis\"></span><p class=\"stem_paragraph \">The formula above can be used to approximate the dew point <span class=\"italic\">D</span>, in degrees Fahrenheit, given the temperature <span class=\"italic\">T</span>, in degrees Fahrenheit, and the relative humidity of <span class=\"italic\">H </span>percent, where <span class=\"math-container\"><img align=\"middle\" role=\"math\" class=\"math-img\" src=\"data:image/png;base64,\" alt=\"H is greater than 50\"></span>. Which of the following expresses the relative humidity in terms of the temperature and the dew point?</p><p>&nbsp;</p></p>\n",
